result.formatted_address: LG/F, Tai Yik House, 27-29 First St, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.name: Burger Joys SYP

reviews.text:
I’ve been a fan of Burger Joys even before they opened their Sai Ying Pun branch and have been to both this store and the one in Wan Chai multiple times throughout these past couple of years. 

I decided to take my colleagues to the SYP branch for lunch since it was closer to our office in Kennedy Town. We arrived at 12 noon and all 7 of us had the restaurant to ourselves, which was quite nice.

Most of us ordered the cheeseburger. I personally got the fish burger with the chocolate milkshake upgrade. All of this arrived fairly quickly with friendly service, though we would’ve appreciated some music during the wait.

Regarding the food itself: although I thoroughly enjoyed the milkshake (always my fave at Burger Joys), I was a bit disappointed by the burger and the fries. It seemed like the fish fillet and fries had been left in the fryer for a little too long, leaving parts of it tough to bite. It was still delicious but the experience wasn’t as great as my previous visits.

In total, I spent $120 ($89 for fish burger set + $31 for milkshake drink upgrade). Pretty steep for lunch, especially considering the quality I got. I think the cheeseburger would’ve been a better choice.

They do have great burgers, the patty literally melts right into your mouth, although the meat flavor is not that impressive(prolly because of the sauce is too strong), the bun is thick and full of butter, sweet and savory. We also ordered a sweet potato chips, and that is my fav, not a lot of restaurants serve sweet potato chips. It is a bit pricey tho.

The double cheese burger is okay. However I'm more impressed by the onion and the pickle in the burger. The onion is extremely fresh and juicy. The pickle is just right and not too sour.

The truffle fries something that's out of my expectation. Instead of simply giving you some fries with a truffle salad dressing for dipping, truffle fries here are actually fries fried with truffle.

The buffalo wings are perhaps a bit too salty for my taste. But it's a good snack if you go with a lot of cold beer or soft drinks!
Pretty good burger, but please update your hours.  Closed @ 21:57?

Burger Joys Sai Ying Pun is spartan and bare-bones: three to four countertops with backless bar stools - and when my boyfriend and visited on a Sunday at 8:00, there were only two staff: one manning the grill and the other taking orders. 

The menu offers a handful of fry-options: sweet potato, an In-n-Out reminiscent animal-fries option, cheese fries. The Southern fried chicken bites were crisp and bite-sized, perfect crabs of batter encompassing juicy and tender nuggets of meat. The classic cheeseburger (at 108HKD), came with a solid-tasting brioche bun, juicy interior, and deliciously oozy melty American cheese. You can add your bougie cheeses, but no one can deny that a good square of yellow American has just the right amount of fat and salt to go perfectly with a medium-rare patty. 

But what I love about Burger Joy’s burger is that the fresh ingredients are snappy and fresh - lettuce is springy, tomatoes are bright and crunchy, and the red onion! Oh the red onion- sharpness cutting through meat. 

Burger Joys is great for a casual no-frills meal - not date-worthy, but plenty perfect for when you don’t need to impress: juice running down your arm and used napkins all over the tray.

經過西環第一街，無意發現樓梯口有一間食漢堡的。
店面不是太大 ， 裝修舒適 ，只有幾排吧檯 。
仲有一個電視添，夜晚過嚟睇波，似乎都幾好。
呢間店專賣burger，即叫即整。Fish Burger魚柳漢堡來到了，厚厚的一大份，非常吸引。
洋蔥及蕃茄 配上魚柳 ，爽脆又新鮮，麵包比較厚，配菜十足，咬起嚟唔覺單調。

result.formatted_address: 301 Queen's Rd W, Sai Ying Pun, Hong Kong
result.name: Electric Ave

reviews.text: I don't usually eat somewhere twice while i'm traveling, but Electric Ave may have me breaking my own rule. My burger was perfect. Melt in your mouth, but not disintegrating in your hand; Juicy, but not greasy; and the perfect amount of cheese for flavor without overwhelming the beef taste. Friendly waiting staff, chill vibe, reasonable price for the fantastic food you get to enjoy. Go see for yourself

This place was legitimately the beat restaurant in Hong Kong. The quality of the food was outstanding on top of personable staff even when they were slammed. Seriously 100HKD for a huge burger, fries, homemade ketchup, and a drink! Everything is homemade here! You may wait a sec for them to get food to you, but trust me it is well worth the wait!
I have been here so many times! The Burgers are world class, freshly made with the best ingredients. Try the chili con carne with fries, it’s spectacular!

I never review, but wow.

Best burger Ive had, perfectly balanced flavours, beautifully put together. Bone marrow potatoes were incredible. Reasonable price with some nice happy hour deals. I got The Stinton. Stop scrolling and just try for yourself.

Great variety, even vegetarian option, their fries are insane, whether it's Rosemary fries or Chilli Fries with homemade sauce. Wonderful service, funny owner, he cracks us up. Superb location too! It's gotta be No. 1 in town.

We sometimes go there all the way from Sai Kung just for their food.

디얼 한구긴분들, 싱글버거와 콜라한캔에 120홍딸을 주고 먹었습니다~! Great~! Awesome~! 이 돈에 이 버거라니 조ㅋ망ㅋ이에요. 
보통 입이 짧고 버거를 좋아해서 여행가면 현지 로컬보다는 버거집을 자주 찾아갑니다. 그리고 그 맛이 있다 없다의 기준은 맥놜 시그니쳐가 되는데 Wonderfull Burger~! 그것과 비교해서 더 훌륭하다고 할 수 있지 않지 있지 않지 있지 않습니다. 사실 구글 검색으로 버거집을 찾고 계신다면 이 하우스 말굥  군쵸 싸쩜 넘눈 거길 갘보ㅋ싴는ㅋ 건 어떨까요?? 사실 거기 가려다 닫혀서 여기온거에요 ㅋㅋㅋㅋ

食物即點即煮，非常夠熱力，吃了Cajun Wings，炸得脆，調味有點辣，洋蔥圈酥脆，炸得透，洋蔥裡面軟了便有少少甜味，甜薯香甜惹味好好吃。

至於兩個漢堡，包裝精緻企理，方便進食，牛肉及其他材料皆新鮮，鐘意熱辣辣牛肉配點涼的洋蔥，冰火相溶。
The veggie burger (mushroom) is pretty decent. Nice take-away place! And they prepare the burgers super quickly!
